LOCUS       Gateway_attB1             25 bp    DNA              UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Gateway attB1 minimal attachment site; 25 bp, the specificity-1 attB
            recombination site appended to a DNA fragment through the attB1 PCR
            primer tail. It recombines with attP1 (BP reaction) to move the
            fragment into a pDONR entry vector. An engineered lambda-derived
            site; the canonical sequence is from Hartley, Temple & Brasch 2000..
